data.enText: a way of referring to sb that you disapprove of because they have right-wing attitudes

tr: an adherent of fascism or other right-wing authoritarian views
relating to or characteristic of fascism

value.def: You use fascist to describe organizations, ideas, or systems which follow the principles of fascism.

example.ex: ...an upsurge of support for extreme rightist, nationalist and fascist organisations.
example.tran: 一股支持极右团体、民族主义者以及法西斯组织的狂潮
法西斯意识形态的凶险本性

posc.def: A fascist is someone who has fascist views.
posc.tran: 法西斯主义者;法西斯分子

value.tran: 法西斯主义的;法西斯的

value.def: If you refer to someone as a fascist, you are expressing disapproval of the fact that they have extreme views on something, and do not tolerate alternative views.

example.ex: ...the so-called health fascists who would meddle in their lives and regulate their calorie intake.
example.tran: 那些可能干涉他们生活、规定他们卡路里摄入量，人称健康法西斯的极端者
